template_reference.name: input_feature_calculator
template_reference.comment:
Mongol double production units get the same score as their non double production counterparts.
There are two main times we consider combat fitness: when producing a unit, and when comparing live units.
When considering mongol double production units from a unit production perspective the additional production utility comes from the fact that these unit productions produce two, so we don't need to accout for the increased "value" in the archetype score.
We will never actually consider "live" double production units from a combat fitness perspective. When a double production spbs is produced, it produces 2 units which are immediately blueprint converted back to the standard counterpart.

list.name: upgrade_bonuses
list.comment: The upgrades of the Japanese towncenter are a mix between offensive and defensive. The first two are more on the defensive side and the third adds a very strong offensive weapon. We list them as offensive for simplicity. That way the scores get calculated and applied similarly to how they are used on a keep. If they are defensive, then the training won't give them proper values because defensive upgrades are expected to be "harmless" without any offensive upgrades in the building.
